Edit: (game has not been updated in almost a year...) Survivalcraft 2 is 100% worth buying. It's one of the best games I've ever played, if not THE best. Survivalcraft 2 puts Minecraft (and ALL other similar games) to shame. Survival mechanics are stellar and totally realistic. There are a few very minor issues with the game, however the developers are great about fixing errors, as they have done many times in the past. (Eg. with the invisible models work around, in the most recent update) These very few errors are: (1) dangerous animals (wolves, coyotes, lions, etc) can spawn inside of completely closed buildings and fences that house your livestock. These dangerous animals can kill your livestock very quickly. (2) Split screen multiplayer controls are slightly glitchy. (This is understandable as the multiplayer feature is new) Other than that, it's a great game. I would suggest adding the ability to add boats that the player can build. (Eg. like a player builds a house, except they'd build a boat)

Look guys, I've been a loyal customer from the beginning. I bought your 
first game when it was broken and basically still in beta. It had a great 
concept. I bought the game once again when I got a new Google Play account. 
When I saw Survivalcraft 2, I had to have it. The only thing that has ever 
bothered me, is that there aren't toggleable NPCs. I love being able to 
create my own stories with this game, but I struggle with the concept that 
I can't create a legitimate Kingdom or commissary sulystem. I understand 
the original concept of the game, but I think it's time to break away from 
that. You guys could get more business that way, I guarantee. Please just 
consider it.

I have put hundreds of hours into Survival Craft but there are some things that really bug me. I just wish there was a custom mode where you can change the world settings that you aren't having fun with, (like losing your levels or the rate at which food decomposes or if you drop your items or not). I don't understand why so many developers dictate their own terms onto the customer. Just a few more options would make the game more enjoyable for everyone. If you are worried about people having it too easy, then why do you have harmless and creative modes? I just feel like the options are too rigid. If you can tell, I just rage quit  because I lost several weeks worth of gatherered materials in about 5 hours and to add insult to injury, I am level 1 again. Here are some of the things that irritate me: Giant magma chambers are apparently more abundant than coal or any other precious ore and the chambers ruined every single one of my mines so far. It seems like you can't go more than 40 blocks in any direction at any depth without discovering a useless giant magma chamber that extends almost as far as the eye can see. It's too easy to die and when you do, you lose HALF of your level and end up being too weak to go back and get the resources you spent weeks in game making sure you had enough food to gather in the first place. Predators just stay near all your items and don't leave. Food rots way too quickly with no method of preservation. Clothes wear out too quickly. Food animals all get killed in the first week by predators; leaving nothing but predators anywhere near your base. Pumpkin soup is just a waste of fuel. You can't get out of the water very easily at all. Leaves stay floating in the air indefinitely. When you freeze,  you can't see anything. Fires get too hot, never last the whole night and do nothing to keep predators away. Compasses require some serious mining to make so if you get killed away from home, you can expect to make a home away from home to survive in for the week or more that it takes you to gather the materials for it, It should just be something simple like an iron rod and a stick. Other than the above problems, It's a good game. I get that the game is about survival and that survival is very tough but some of the above have the potential to sap the fun out of what would be a good game ;quite quickly. The furniture creation is a great addition but I wish that I could transfer items from my creative map to my challenging map.

No contest the best  This game can actually not be compared to minecraft, since it is so much better. I have MC as well and it is a bore. SC is much more challenging and immersive than MC. In MC surviving is no challenge and you can run away from each and every mob. In SC you cannot run away from a lion, rhino, bear, tiger, wolves, hyena etc. MC does not even have flying animals. The creative options are so much more and the furniture or rather custom blocks are insane.  The price is no contest. In MC you have to pay to get new textures, I think you have to pay to fart as well. In SC there are so many custom textures and all are free and is easy to make yourself. With MC you need mods that almost always causes your game to crash and lock up, even the textures do that. In SC you do not need mods, since everything is already great. The pistons are way way better than MC. Now we are just waiting for multiplayer, which will be the next big update. Controls are also way easier to use.  The old buttons are available as an option as well though, but pads work better.  MC is for fantasy lovers, SC is for people who like realistic games.
